=head1 DESCRIPTION

The properties of a managed product, such as an Amazon Web Services
Managed Rules rule group or an Amazon Web Services Marketplace managed
rule group.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 IsAdvancedManagedRuleSet => Bool

Indicates whether the rule group provides an advanced set of
protections, such as the the Amazon Web Services Managed Rules rule
groups that are used for WAF intelligent threat mitigation.


=head2 IsVersioningSupported => Bool

Indicates whether the rule group is versioned.


=head2 ManagedRuleSetName => Str

The name of the managed rule group. For example,
C<AWSManagedRulesAnonymousIpList> or C<AWSManagedRulesATPRuleSet>.


=head2 ProductDescription => Str

A short description of the managed rule group.


=head2 ProductId => Str

A unique identifier for the rule group. This ID is returned in the
responses to create and list commands. You provide it to operations
like update and delete.


=head2 ProductLink => Str

For Amazon Web Services Marketplace managed rule groups only, the link
to the rule group product page.


=head2 ProductTitle => Str

The display name for the managed rule group. For example, C<Anonymous
IP list> or C<Account takeover prevention>.


=head2 SnsTopicArn => Str

The Amazon resource name (ARN) of the Amazon Simple Notification
Service SNS topic that's used to provide notification of changes to the
managed rule group. You can subscribe to the SNS topic to receive
notifications when the managed rule group is modified, such as for new
versions and for version expiration. For more information, see the
Amazon Simple Notification Service Developer Guide
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/sns/latest/dg/welcome.html).


=head2 VendorName => Str

The name of the managed rule group vendor. You use this, along with the
rule group name, to identify a rule group.



